Bayelsa State Governor, Duoye Diri has arrived the Supreme Court for the retirement court session in honour of Justice Mary Ekaego Peter Odili. Diri stormed the Apex Court few minutes past 8 for the special court session scheduled for 10 a.m. He was sighted with his predecessor, Seriake Dickson and accompanied to the court with a retinue of top aides and security operatives. DAILY POST recalls that Justice Odili delivered the landmark judgment that ushered in Governor Diri following the nullification of election of Mr David Lyon
of the All Progressives Congress, APC, due to discrepancies in the names and certificate of his deputy. At the time of this report, the apex court has been jam-packed with Judges, senior lawyers and government functionaries seeking to honour the eminent jurist on her retirement from Nigeriaâ€™s Judiciary. Also, armed security operatives have taken positions in the court premises to prevent security breaches.